						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Hero-stone standing near the Īśvara temple.</hi></p>						

						<p>Siṁghaṇa—A.D. 1235.</p>						

						<p>This inscription is dated in the cyclic year <hi rend="bold">[Jaya]</hi> in the reign of <hi rend="bold">Simhaṇadēva,</hi> (regnal year lost), <hi rend="bold">Māgha s11u. 3, Monday.</hi> During the reign of Siṁghaṇa, the cyclic year Jaya coincided with A.D. 1234-35, in which year the details correspond to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1235, January 22, Monday, f.d.t. ·35.</hi></p>						

						<p>It records the death of a hero named <hi rend="bold">Jakkayya,</hi> son of <hi rend="bold">Bairaḍiya Mādayya,</hi> while rescuing the cattle. The village <hi rend="bold">Sarevūr</hi> is mentioned.</p>						

						</summary>
